<div class="recipe-container">
    <h1>Gobi Manchurian</h1>

    <div class="recipe-description">
        <p><strong>Gobi Manchurian</strong> is a popular Indo-Chinese dish made with crispy cauliflower florets tossed in a spicy, tangy, and flavorful Manchurian sauce. This dish is perfect as a starter or a side dish for fried rice or noodles.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ingredients">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <div class="ingredient-list">
            <div class="ingredient-item">
                <p><strong>For Frying Cauliflower:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups Cauliflower florets</li>
                    <li>1/2 cup All-purpose flour</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Corn flour</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Black pepper powder</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Red chili powder</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Salt</li>
                    <li>1/2 cup Water</li>
                    <li>Oil for deep frying</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="ingredient-item">
                <p><strong>For Manchurian Sauce:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 tbsp Oil</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Garlic (minced)</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Ginger (minced)</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Onion (finely chopped)</li>
                    <li>1/4 cup Capsicum (diced)</li>
                    <li>2 tbsp Soy sauce</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Chili sauce</li>
                    <li>1 tbsp Tomato ketchup</li>
                    <li>1/2 tsp Vinegar</li>
                    <li>1 tsp Corn flour mixed with 2 tbsp water</li>
                    <li>Spring onions for garnish</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cooking-instructions">
        <h2>How to Cook</h2>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Blanch the Cauliflower:</strong> Boil cauliflower florets in salted water for 5 minutes. Drain and keep aside.</li>
            <li><strong>Prepare the Batter:</strong> In a bowl, mix all-purpose flour, corn flour, red chili powder, black pepper, and salt. Add water gradually to make a smooth batter.</li>
            <li><strong>Deep Fry:</strong> Heat oil in a pan. Dip cauliflower in the batter and deep fry until golden and crispy. Drain on paper towels.</li>
            <li><strong>Prepare Manchurian Sauce:</strong> Heat 2 tbsp oil in a wok. Add garlic, ginger, and onions. Sauté for a minute.</li>
            <li><strong>Add Vegetables & Sauces:</strong> Add capsicum, soy sauce, chili sauce, tomato ketchup, and vinegar. Stir well.</li>
            <li><strong>Thicken the Sauce:</strong> Add the corn flour slurry (corn flour + water) and cook until the sauce thickens.</li>
            <li><strong>Toss the Cauliflower:</strong> Add the fried cauliflower and mix well so that it is coated with the sauce.</li>
            <li><strong>Garnish & Serve:</strong> Garnish with chopped spring onions and serve hot.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="tips">
        <h2>Tips & Variations</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>For extra crispiness, double-fry the cauliflower.</li>
            <li>Add a pinch of sugar to balance flavors.</li>
            <li>Use a mix of red and green bell peppers for color.</li>
            <li>For a dry version, use less corn flour slurry.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="serve">
        <h2>Serving Suggestions</h2>
        <p>Gobi Manchurian tastes best when served hot with fried rice, noodles, or as a standalone appetizer.</p>
    </div>
</div>
